---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="About - Matthew Windham"
	description="A little about Matthew Windham, DevOps engineer in Austin, Texas."
>
	<main class="wrap">
		<div class="about-head">
			<img class="avatar" src="/avatar.jpg" width="140" height="140" alt="Matthew Windham" />
			<h1>About</h1>
		</div>

		<section class="bio">
			<p>
				I grew up in Montana and studied Geoscience at the University of Montana. It took a while
				to admit that what I was actually most interested in wasn't the rocks — it was the systems.
				Pipelines, configurations, the way things break and how you make them not break. That
				realization eventually led me to Austin, TX, where I've spent the last several years
				building infrastructure for a living.
			</p>
			<p>
				The part of the job I keep coming back to is automation: finding the thing someone has to
				do manually and making it disappear. There's something satisfying about a deploy that used
				to take an afternoon becoming a single click, or a flaky process that required babysitting
				becoming something you can forget exists. The best infrastructure is boring — reliable
				enough that nobody has to think about it.
			</p>
			<p>
				I'm also genuinely curious about tooling. I'd rather build something with a new technology
				and see how it breaks than read about it. That mindset has sent me down a lot of rabbit
				holes, most recently around AI tooling — using it in daily workflows since 2025, with
				Claude Code CLI becoming part of the infrastructure work since February 2026.
			</p>
			<p>
				Outside of work: married, we have a dog, and most weekends you'll find me on a golf course
				somewhere in Texas. Montana gave me an appreciation for being outside; golf is how I
				maintain that without needing to drive six hours to a trailhead.
			</p>
			<blockquote>
				"If a human operator needs to touch your system during normal operations, you have a bug.
				The definition of normal changes as your systems grow."
				<cite>— Carla Geisser, Google SRE</cite>
			</blockquote>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-head {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1.75rem;
		padding-top: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.avatar {
		width: 140px;
		height: 140px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		object-fit: cover;
		object-position: center top;
		border: 2px solid rgba(255, 153, 0, 0.35);
		box-shadow: 0 0 32px rgba(255, 153, 0, 0.12);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.bio p {
		color: var(--text-dim);
		line-height: 1.75;
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		max-width: 62ch;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.about-head {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
			gap: 1rem;
		}

		.avatar {
			width: 100px;
			height: 100px;
		}
	}
</style>
